The paper discusses a mathematical framework for hyperparameter optimization and meta-learning, which are both topics within the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of TensorFlow, a popular deep learning framework, which suggests a focus on deep learning and neural networks, placing it in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the optimization of learning rates, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of sufficient conditions for convergence suggests a focus on optimization and control, placing it in the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
